A cyclone weather system off Madagascar has caused storm surf along Durban s North Beach forcing the authorities to close the beach while large waves batter the beachfront, reports the Berea Mail.Rescue Care were at the beachfront earlier this afternoon and shared some photos of the stormy surf:Spectators made their way down to North Beach to view crashing waves spill over the promenade on Durban s North Beach.A view of the monster waves crashing on Durban s North Beach as a result of the cyclone weather system: Caxton News Service&nbsp;Read original story on bereamail.co.za